EXTRACT.P:
This protocol is a procedure for using portable electrochemical (EC) cells for measuring carbon monoxide (CO) and oxygen (O
2
) concentrations in controlled and uncontrolled emissions from existing stationary 4-stroke lean burn and 4-stroke rich burn reciprocating internal combustion engines as specified in the applicable rule.

This protocol measures the engine exhaust gas concentrations of carbon monoxide (CO) and oxygen (O
2
).
